original: Andersson, Olle Laurentius, kyrkoherde, Gamleby, f. 20/6/03 i Augerum, Blek. 1., av köpm. A. J. A. o. h. h. G. 28 m. Dagmar Engvall. Barn: Lars f. 29, Ulla 30, Kerstin 33, Eva 36. — Stud:ex. i Karlskrona 21, fil. kand. 24, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Linköp. stift 27. V. kommin. i Rönö 27, kommin. där 28, kyrkoadj. i S :t Johannes församl. i Norrköp. 32, kyrkoh. i Västra Harg 38, i Gamleby sed. 44. Pens:styr. ombud sed. 45.
translated: Andersson, Olle Laurentius, Parish Priest of Gamleby, born on June 20, 1903 in Augerum, Blekinge. The first child of merchant A.J.A. and homemaker G. 28 married to Dagmar Engvall. Children: Lars born in 1929, Ulla in 1930, Kerstin in 1933, and Eva in 1936. He passed his high school exams in Karlskrona in 1921, received a Bachelor of Arts degree in 1924, Bachelor of Theology in 1927, and completed practical theological trials and was ordained in the Linköping Diocese in 1927. He was a curate in Rönö in 1927, curate in 1928, church adjutant in St. John's parish in Norrköping in 1932, parish priest in Västra Harg in 1938, and parish priest in Gamleby since 1944. He has been a pension fund representative since 1945.
